[It is fairly busy out there so it is hard to get additional information.
However, the 300 workers at The Sun have been sent home with 15 days of
ciprofloxacin. A positive swab was obtained from Steven's computer
keyboard. How many other environmental samples were taken in his office and
desk is not known. The circumstances for the second positive are unclear
but it seems at this time that he was found when all Steven's coworkers
were nasally swabbed, suggesting that he was well at the time, but this is
speculation until there is more information; alternative readings would
have him ill at the time he was swabbed. When one considers the timing of
Steven's illness -- he started to feel ill on Sunday September 30th, drove
back to Lake Worth on the 1st October and into hospital the next morning,
the shortest co-exposure would have been on Tuesday 25th or Wednesday 26th
September and his colleague's nose is (still) positive 11 days later. -
Mod.MHJ
