<promed@promedmail.org>
[At a time like this people will do some strange and nasty things to take
advantage of the hysteria of the moment. There has been no confirmation on
this story as to a real risk. It has all the hallmarks of a very nasty
hoax. There have been a number of people examined to see if they had
anthrax but none were clinically or microbiologically confirmed -- other
than this one fellow with a positive nasal swab. All such reports of white
powders in the mail should regarded with skepticism until there is hard
evidence of a real risk. And such envelopes should be referred immediately
to the police for appropriate action. - Mod.MHJ
